    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/export-tag-syntax-validation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The system we devised uses an extra layer of tags inserted into an existing data spreadsheet at specific locations that tell the extract command how to transform the data sections of the sheet (i.e., data tables) into key-based records representable in both JSON format and a relational database.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes tagging system and extraction process but does not explicitly document a separate pre-extraction tag syntax validation step. The paper shows tags are parsed during extraction ('The heart of the extract module is a tag parser that identifies pound-delimited tags'), not validated beforehand. Validation in MESSES refers to JSON Schema validation of extracted data, not tag syntax validation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo13070842",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "export-tag-syntax-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Validates that tagged column headers in tabular export files conform to MESSES tag syntax (formats like #<table_name>.id and #.<field_name>) before attempting JSON conversion. This ensures malformed or inconsistent tags are caught early, preventing downstream JSON structure corru",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:10:41.048176+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/export-tag-syntax-validation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The heart of the extract module is a tag parser that identifies pound-delimited tags which direct the extraction of data from tabular files as tags and associated data are parsed.",
      "asbval:note": "Tag parsing occurs during extraction, not as a separate pre-validation step. The paper describes error feedback at validation step: 'MESSES provides warning and error feedback for the user at each step, especially the validation step' but this refers to JSON Schema validation post-extraction, not tag syntax validation pre-extraction.",
