    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/matrix-directive-collation-validation/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The MESSES package enables the overall capture, validation, and conversion process using three major commands: 'extract', 'validate', and 'convert'. The convert module is broken into more pieces. The convert.py submodule implements the convert command, the convert_schema.py submodule holds the schemas and schema templates in JSON Schema format for the command, the user_input_checking.py submodule validates conversion directives, and there are submodules for the built-in conversion directives and specific code for each supported conversion format.",
      "asbval:note": "MESSES is confirmed as a tool with convert command and conversion directives. The paper confirms it is a Python package with CLI.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo13070842",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "matrix-directive-collation-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MESSES as command-line tool and Python library that executes the convert command to apply matrix directives",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:12:14.144872+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/matrix-directive-collation-validation/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MESSES uses the jsonschema library to validate user JSON input against an expected schema generated by MESSES in JSON Schema format. The Protocol Dependent Schema (PD schema) and Experiment Description Specification base schema (EDS base schema) provide the bulk of the final integrated schema in JSON Schema format that is used for validation via the jsonschema library.",
      "asbval:note": "jsonschema is confirmed to validate JSON against schemas including EDS base schema. However, the paper does not specifically mention validation of 'collation directive output' \u2014 only general JSON validation against schemas.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo13070842",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "matrix-directive-collation-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "jsonschema validates the JSON structure of measurement records and the output of the collation directive against the Experiment Description Specification schema",
