      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MESSES uses the jsonschema library to validate user JSON input against an expected schema generated by MESSES in JSON Schema format... The Protocol Dependent Schema (PD schema) and Experiment Description Specification base schema (EDS base schema) provide the bulk of the final integrated schema in JSON Schema format that is used for validation via the jsonschema library.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms jsonschema validates against PD schema and EDS base schema, but does NOT mention filtering or sorting as part of jsonschema's role. The claim conflates validation with filtering/sorting, which are separate operations in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo13070842",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "tabular-record-filtering-and-sorting",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[2].role",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Validation library used by MESSES to ensure filtered and sorted JSON records conform to Experiment Description Specification and Protocol Dependent Schema",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:14:37.336018+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/unit-test-design-for-data-processing/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Each module and submodule include unit-tests that test all critical functions. Every function in every module is tested to make sure it gives the expected output when it should and errors when it should. Every command and associated command line option are tested, for example, the update and override options for the convert command.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes unit testing of extraction, validation, and conversion operations.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo13070842",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "unit-test-design-for-data-processing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Design and implement unit tests to validate the correctness of data extraction, validation, and conversion operations in tabular-to-JSON pipelines.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:14:51.237459+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/unit-test-design-for-data-processing/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The 'modification' part is used to modify record values. It can be used to prepend, append, delete, overwrite, or regex substitute values... MESSES uses the jsonschema library to validate user JSON input against an expected schema generated by MESSES in JSON Schema format.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes modification directives and schema validation but does not explicitly name 'code' directive or 'record_id resolution' as tested directive types. Paper mentions 'code' evaluation is not explicitly documented in passages; only modification operations (prepend, append, delete, overwrite, regex) are detailed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo13070842",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "unit-test-design-for-data-processing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "directive handlers (e.g., str, code, record_id resolution) and schema-based transformations produce expected outputs",
